properties.headline: Small Craft Advisory issued January 3 at 2:32PM CST until January 5 at 12:00PM CST by NWS Milwaukee/Sullivan WI
properties.description:
...STRONG WINDS ACROSS THE LAKE SUNDAY AND SUNDAY NIGHT...

* WHAT...For the Small Craft Advisory, west winds gusting to 20 to
30 kts. For the Gale Watch, west winds 15 to 25 kt with gusts
up to 40 kt possible.

* WHERE...Sheboygan to Port Washington WI, Port Washington to
North Point Light WI, North Point Light to Wind Point WI and
Wind Point WI to Winthrop Harbor IL.

* WHEN...For the Small Craft Advisory, from 6 AM to noon CST
Sunday. For the Gale Watch, from Sunday afternoon through late
Sunday night.

* IMPACTS...Strong winds can cause hazardous waves which could
capsize or damage vessels and reduce visibility.
properties.instruction:
Mariners should consider altering plans to avoid possible
hazardous conditions.  Remain in port, seek safe harbor, alter
course, and/or secure the vessel for severe wind and waves.

NWSheadline: SMALL CRAFT ADVISORY IN EFFECT FROM 6 AM TO NOON CST SUNDAY... ...GALE WATCH IN EFFECT FROM SUNDAY AFTERNOON THROUGH LATE SUNDAY NIGHT
